North West Correctional Services and police are hot on their heels of 10 dangerous awaiting-trial prisoners who escaped from Mogwase prison.Correctional Services spokesperson Manelisi Wolela says the offenders have committed serious offences. Just after midnight the 10 awaiting trial detainees broke through the facility and escaped in the evening,&#8221; Manelisi said.Manelisi added that no one has been re-arrested but the department has issued a warning to all people to be on the lookout and be careful not to interfere with these escapees, because some of them have committed serious offences.The department said that they working hard with South African Police Srvice to search the ten awaiting trial prisoners.SABC